    explanation: 'The most likely cause of this error message is that either the S3 bucket policy or IAM role configuration has an error or simply does not grant the required permissions. The DevOps engineer should review the bucket policy or associated IAM user policies for any statements that might be denying access. The engineer should also verify that the requests to the bucket meet any conditions in the bucket policy or IAM policies, checking for any incorrect deny statements, missing actions, or incorrect spacing in the policy. CORRECT: "The bucket policy does not grant permission" is a correct answer (as explained above.) CORRECT: "There is an issue with the IAM role configuration" is also a correct answer (as explained above.) INCORRECT: "Default encryption is enabled on the S3 bucket" is incorrect. This would not affect access to the object as the object would be automatically decrypted by S3. INCORRECT: "The object has been moved to Amazon Glacier" is incorrect. With Glacier an AccessDeniedException error would be received if permission is not granted. INCORRECT: "S3 versioning is enabled on the S3 bucket" is incorrect. Versioning does not affect access permissions to an object. References: https://aws.amazon.com/premiumsupport/knowledge-center/s3-troubleshoot-403/ Save time with our AWS cheat sheets: https://digitalcloud.training/amazon-s3-and-glacier/'
